hh3cLicense.name: hh3cLicense

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

hh3cLicense.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Haidian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cLicense.description: This MIB is used to manage license, including license key, activation key and activation file.

hh3cLicenseNotifyEnable.name: hh3cLicenseNotifyEnable
hh3cLicenseNotifyEnable.description: This object indicates whether the notifications of license should be generated.

hh3cLicenseOpEntryMaxNum.name: hh3cLicenseOpEntryMaxNum
hh3cLicenseOpEntryMaxNum.description: This object indicates the maximum number of entries that may be held in hh3cLicenseOpEntry. When the number of entries in hh3cLicenseOpEntry reached the value of this object, the oldest entry would be destroyed automatic after executing a new operation.

hh3cLicenseNextFreeOpIndex.name: hh3cLicenseNextFreeOpIndex
hh3cLicenseNextFreeOpIndex.description: This object indicates the appropriate value for hh3cLicenseOpIndex that can be used to create an entry in hh3cLicenseOpTable.

hh3cLicenseDevInfoTable.name: hh3cLicenseDevInfoTable
hh3cLicenseDevInfoTable.description: A table that displays device information which use to apply license.

hh3cLicenseDevInfoEntry.name: hh3cLicenseDevInfoEntry
hh3cLicenseDevInfoEntry.description: A set of objects that displays device information of license.

hh3cLicensePhysicalIndex.name: hh3cLicensePhysicalIndex
hh3cLicensePhysicalIndex.description: The entPhysicalIndex of the device. The meaning of this object is associated with the management state which from hh3cLicenseInstallType. Note that: 1) hh3cLicenseInstallType is installInChassis. This object represents the entPhysicalIndex of the local active MPU. 2) hh3cLicenseInstallType is installInSlot. This object represents the entPhysicalIndex of MPU boards. 3) hh3cLicenseInstallType is installInCPU. This object represents the entPhysicalIndex of the CPUs on an MPU board.

hh3cLicenseSN.name: hh3cLicenseSN
hh3cLicenseSN.description: The serial number of the device.

hh3cLicenseDeviceIDType.name: hh3cLicenseDeviceIDType
hh3cLicenseDeviceIDType.description: The types of device ID. invalid - The device ID is invalid. keyString - The device ID is a string. file - The device ID is a file.

hh3cLicenseDeviceID.name: hh3cLicenseDeviceID
hh3cLicenseDeviceID.description: A string represents the device ID. For example: Device ID: XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX This object can not be read when hh3cLicenseDeviceIDType is invalid, and a file name with full path while hh3cLicenseDeviceIDType is file. For example: Device ID: flash:/xxx.did

hh3cLicenseHardwareInfo.name: hh3cLicenseHardwareInfo
hh3cLicenseHardwareInfo.description: The information of the device hardware.

hh3cLicenseMaxNum.name: hh3cLicenseMaxNum
hh3cLicenseMaxNum.description: The max number of licenses that can be installed in device.

hh3cLicenseRecyclableNum.name: hh3cLicenseRecyclableNum
hh3cLicenseRecyclableNum.description: The number of recyclable storage for licenses.

hh3cLicenseInstallType.name: hh3cLicenseInstallType
hh3cLicenseInstallType.description: The state of license management. This object determines the instance of hh3cLicensePhysicalIndex and hh3cLicenseOpPhysicalIndex. invalid - The state is invalid as driver fault. installInChassis - License is chassis locked. installInSlot - License is MPU locked. installInCPU - License is CPU locked.

hh3cLicenseFileStoragePath.name: hh3cLicenseFileStoragePath
hh3cLicenseFileStoragePath.description: The storage path of the installed license files.

hh3cLicenseGeneralTable.name: hh3cLicenseGeneralTable
hh3cLicenseGeneralTable.description: A table that displays general information of installed license.

hh3cLicenseGeneralEntry.name: hh3cLicenseGeneralEntry
hh3cLicenseGeneralEntry.description: A set of objects that displays general information of installed license.

hh3cLicenseIndex.name: hh3cLicenseIndex
hh3cLicenseIndex.description: ID that can be used to uniquely identify a license. It may use a stable storage index.

hh3cLicenseFeature.name: hh3cLicenseFeature
hh3cLicenseFeature.description: The name of the licensed feature. When there multiple features, this object will display with space as delimiter.

hh3cLicenseProductDescr.name: hh3cLicenseProductDescr
hh3cLicenseProductDescr.description: The product description in a license.

hh3cLicenseFileDescr.name: hh3cLicenseFileDescr
hh3cLicenseFileDescr.description: The file description in activation file.

hh3cLicenseState.name: hh3cLicenseState
hh3cLicenseState.description: The state of an installed license. invalid - The license is invalid and cannot be used. inuse - The license is being used. usable - The license is available for use. 1. If multiple days-restricted licenses for one feature are installed, only one license is in 'inuse' state and the rest licenses are in 'usable' state. 2. A date-restricted license is in this state if its start date is not reached. expired - The license has expired. uninstalled - The license has been uninstalled. unusable - The license cannot be used.

hh3cLicenseActivationFile.name: hh3cLicenseActivationFile
hh3cLicenseActivationFile.description: The name of an installed activation file, with device name and file name. For example: flash:/license/210231A1V0A1290000012013032718261184345.ak

hh3cLicenseActivationKey.name: hh3cLicenseActivationKey
hh3cLicenseActivationKey.description: The activation key that has been installed. For example: Activation Key: dyKT-x3vc-W@Ca-n4gn-Yo83-rVY3-C8:7-e3pg

hh3cLicenseLicenseKey.name: hh3cLicenseLicenseKey
hh3cLicenseLicenseKey.description: The license key that has been installed.

hh3cLicenseUninstActivationFile.name: hh3cLicenseUninstActivationFile
hh3cLicenseUninstActivationFile.description: If an activation file is uninstalled, the system creates an uninstall file. Use this file together with the SN and DID of the transfer destination to register the license for the transfer destination.

hh3cLicenseUninstActivationKey.name: hh3cLicenseUninstActivationKey
hh3cLicenseUninstActivationKey.description: If an activation key is uninstalled, the system creates an uninstall key. Use this key together with the SN and DID of the transfer destination to register the license for the transfer destination.

hh3cLicenseType.name: hh3cLicenseType
hh3cLicenseType.description: License type by validity period. unknown - The system cannot obtain the license type. permanent - Purchased license that never expires and is always valid. daysRestricted - Purchased license that is valid for a period in days. trialDaysRestricted - Free trial license that is valid for a period in days. dateRestricted - Purchased license that is valid for an absolute date range. trialDateRestricted - Free trial license that is valid for an absolute date range. countRestricted - Purchased license that is valid for several useing times. trialCountRestricted - Free trial license that is valid for several useing times.

hh3cLicenseInstalledTime.name: hh3cLicenseInstalledTime
hh3cLicenseInstalledTime.description: Time when the license was installed. For example, it would be displayed as: 2013-9-20,13:30:15.0

hh3cLicenseUninstalledTime.name: hh3cLicenseUninstalledTime
hh3cLicenseUninstalledTime.description: The time when the license was uninstalled. For example, it would be displayed as: 2013-9-26,15:12:20.0

hh3cLicenseDaysLeft.name: hh3cLicenseDaysLeft
hh3cLicenseDaysLeft.description: Remaining days of the license. This object is available for a days-restricted license.

hh3cLicenseValidityStart.name: hh3cLicenseValidityStart
hh3cLicenseValidityStart.description: Start date for a date-restricted license. This object is available for a date-restricted license. But if the start date is not limited, this object is unavailable. For example, it would be displayed as: 2013-9-26,15:12:20.0

hh3cLicenseValidityEnd.name: hh3cLicenseValidityEnd
hh3cLicenseValidityEnd.description: End date for a date-restricted license. This object is available for a date-restricted license. But if the end date is not limited, this object is unavailable. For example, it would be displayed as: 2014-9-26,15:12:20.0

hh3cLicenseExpiredDays.name: hh3cLicenseExpiredDays
hh3cLicenseExpiredDays.description: Passed days after a license has been expired.

hh3cLicenseCount.name: hh3cLicenseCount
hh3cLicenseCount.description: The effective number of license. This object is available for a count-restricted license.

hh3cLicenseFeatureTable.name: hh3cLicenseFeatureTable
hh3cLicenseFeatureTable.description: A table that displays installed licenses for features.

hh3cLicenseFeatureEntry.name: hh3cLicenseFeatureEntry
hh3cLicenseFeatureEntry.description: A set of objects that displays installed licenses for features.

hh3cLicenseFeatureName.name: hh3cLicenseFeatureName
hh3cLicenseFeatureName.description: Feature that must be licensed before being used.

hh3cLicenseFeatureState.name: hh3cLicenseFeatureState
hh3cLicenseFeatureState.description: License type by purchasing state. notLicensed - The feature is not licensed. trialLicense - The feature is using trial license. formalLicense - The feature is using purchased license.

hh3cLicenseOpTable.name: hh3cLicenseOpTable
hh3cLicenseOpTable.description: A table that used to install or uninstall license.

hh3cLicenseOpEntry.name: hh3cLicenseOpEntry
hh3cLicenseOpEntry.description: A set of objects used to install or uninstall license.

hh3cLicenseOpIndex.name: hh3cLicenseOpIndex
hh3cLicenseOpIndex.description: ID that can be used to uniquely identify an operation.

hh3cLicenseOpPhysicalIndex.name: hh3cLicenseOpPhysicalIndex
hh3cLicenseOpPhysicalIndex.description: This object indicates that the entPhysicalIndex of the device where the operation is being executed. The meaning of this object is associated with the management state from hh3cLicenseInstallType. Note that: 1) hh3cLicenseInstallType is installInChassis. This object represents the entPhysicalIndex of chassis local master. 2) hh3cLicenseInstallType is installInSlot. This object represents the entPhysicalIndex of MPU boards. 3) hh3cLicenseInstallType is installInCPU. This object represents the entPhysicalIndex of CPUs. This object must be set and can not be set to zero when executing an operation.

hh3cLicenseOpType.name: hh3cLicenseOpType
hh3cLicenseOpType.description: The type of this operation. compress - Compress the license storage if the free license storage is not sufficient. Note that: 1) After compressing, the expired licenses and uninstalled licenses in the storage area will be cleared. 2) The DID changes each time the license storage is compressed. 3) Before performing a compression, make sure all activation files generated based on the old DID have been installed. They cannot be installed after the compression. delete - Compress one license storage only. installActivationFile - Install an activation file. installActivationKey - Install an activation key. installLicenseKey - Install a license key. uninstallActivationFile - Uninstall an activation file. uninstallActivationKey - Uninstall an activation key. uninstallLicenseKey - Uninstall a license key.

hh3cLicenseOpString.name: hh3cLicenseOpString
hh3cLicenseOpString.description: This object might be an activation file name, an activation key or a license key that is to be installed, uninstalled or deleted. The operation type is specified in hh3cLicenseOpType. For compressing, this object must not be bound when creating a row. For deletion, this object could be an activation file, an activation key or a license key. For installActivationFile and uninstallActivationFile, this object must be a name of an activation file, with full path. Such as: flash:/license/210231A1V0A1290000012013032718261184345.ak For installActivationKey and uninstallActivationKey, this object must be an activation key. For installLicenseKey and uninstallLicenseKey, this object must be a license key.

hh3cLicenseOpNotifyEnable.name: hh3cLicenseOpNotifyEnable
hh3cLicenseOpNotifyEnable.description: This object indicates whether 'hh3cLicenseOpCompletion' notifications will be generated after this operation is completed. Note that, this object is meaningless if the value of 'hh3cLicenseNotifyEnable' is 'false'.

hh3cLicenseOpRowStatus.name: hh3cLicenseOpRowStatus
hh3cLicenseOpRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. When an entry was in active status, values of any object in this entry are forbidden to be changed.

hh3cLicenseOpState.name: hh3cLicenseOpState
hh3cLicenseOpState.description: The state of this operation. opInProgress - This operation is in progress. opSuccessful - Successful to execute this operation. opFailed - Failed to execute this operation, and 'hh3cLicenseOpFailedReason' will indicate the detailed cause of the failure.

hh3cLicenseOpFailedReason.name: hh3cLicenseOpFailedReason
hh3cLicenseOpFailedReason.description: This object indicates the detailed cause of the failure when this operation failed.

hh3cLicenseOpEndTime.name: hh3cLicenseOpEndTime
hh3cLicenseOpEndTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the operation is done.

hh3cLicenseOpCompletion.name: hh3cLicenseOpCompletion
hh3cLicenseOpCompletion.description: This notification is generated when a license operation completed.

hh3cLicenseActivationFileLost.name: hh3cLicenseActivationFileLost
hh3cLicenseActivationFileLost.description: This notification is generated when the activation file has been lost.

hh3cLicenseActivationFileRestored.name: hh3cLicenseActivationFileRestored
hh3cLicenseActivationFileRestored.description: This notification is generated when the activation file restored successfully.

hh3cLicenseExpired.name: hh3cLicenseExpired
hh3cLicenseExpired.description: This notification is generated when the license expires.

hh3cLicenseExpireWarning.name: hh3cLicenseExpireWarning
hh3cLicenseExpireWarning.description: This notification is generated when is about to expire.

hh3cLicenseBindValidityPeriodRemaining.name: hh3cLicenseBindValidityPeriodRemaining
hh3cLicenseBindValidityPeriodRemaining.description: This object indicates the remaining days before the feature's license expires.
